01/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Combating terrorism and enhancing security will be the focus of a meeting that kicks off Monday (1 September) on the northern Adriatic island of Brijuni.
President Stipe Mesic, Parliamentary Speaker Zlatko Tomcic and members of parliament's committee for home policy and national security will be attending, along with representatives of NATO and the EU.
In other news, the Croatian island of Sipan near Dubrovnik is hosting the annual international seminar on NATO and South East Europe (SEE), which opens Monday.
Government officials, media representatives and postgraduate students from SEE countries and NATO member states will be attending.
(HINA, BBC - 31/08/03)
